e several other mobs you have to kill repeatedly in the hopes they finally cough up the required item.<br><br>The 1 handers are 14/24 with pretty good stats and procs.  However, I'm looking at the big 24 and wishing it was more like 20.  The 2 hander is nice, but not many warriors use 2h slashers, and with the 51/42 axe you get from ToV (that right?), why would you use the epic?  I'm thinking if you have the resources to complete your epic, this axe is attainable as well.<br><br>Do the epics have damage bonus modifiers which make them more appealing given the length of the delay?  What am I missing here?<br><br>This isn't a gripe post.  I'd really like to hear from some warriors with their epics on the overall battle value of these blades. <p><P><img src=http://zencore.home.mindspring.com/kleg.gif><P><BR>56 Myrmidon Tanklet and Officer of the Valiant Crusaders, equipped with built-in fear<BR>"The more you drink, the better I look!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugerfs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gerfs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 6:23:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Epic - is it worth it?</span><hr size=1> IMO the war epic isnt worth it... There are many weapons out there that are better.  Swiftblade of zek wich is 11/18 10ac and other stats (i think its 11/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  you can usually buy for 90k but this is just my opinion. <p>Gerf WolfraffianA.K.A The President<br>60 Warlord "Eternal Wrath"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utremainbladesinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TremainBladesinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 6:25:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theunholytrinity.org/cracks_smileys/cwm/big/firemad.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Epic - is it worth it?</span><hr size=1> Is it worth doing? yes.  Is it worth spending 150k on? no way. <p>"the day i die will be the day i shut my mouth and put down my sword" - Tremain, 55 Myrmidon</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 6:39:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Epic - is it worth it?</span><hr size=1> You guys understand that a 10/20 and a 10/25 weapon eventually approach the same delay under good haste, right?<br><br>You'd rather have a 13/26 than a 10/20 under good haste, as they'll both approach minimum delay.<br><br>14/24, properly hasted is nearly as fast as any other sword in the game. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,Guildleader: <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a>, Grandmaster <a href=http://www.base-nine.org/available_tinkering_items.htm>Tinkerer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugazamel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gazamel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 6:45:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://arizona.speedchoice.com/~bbalatgek/pics/personal2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Epic - is it worth it?</span><hr size=1> It's a matter of why you're doing the quest.  I did mine long ago when the epics were pretty much the best thing out there.  <br><br>If you use both, the stats are like this:<br><br>str 20, dex 55, stam 15, hps 100, all resists +10 , +40 atk, with a 100dd proc on whichever hand you hold the blade of strategy (175dd proc, no atk bonus, and only +15 dex on the 2h version)<br><br>So yeah, if you're not able to get high-end kael or NToV weapons, these swords are well worth it.  Is it worth paying 150k for the green scale?  IMO, no, get your guild to go keel Severilous <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It makes you feel like you earned it more if you do it that way <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9226">Gazamel</a><BR>Gnome Warlord<BR>Vea Victis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=varulvthewarrior>Varulv the Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 6:57:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> My thoughts on the Epics.<br><br>I think they are very well worth it, especially if you dont have the power to do NToV like Gazamel stated.<br><br>The proc on Blade of strategy adds ALOT of hate to you, it is a great weapon for a main tank, and with the added dex you get in total with the two warrior blades you proc alot.<br><br>I have had the possibility to use Swiftblade of zek, I just dont feel it is worth it. Epic is better then that one in my opinion. Many others disagree, but that is atleast what I think.<br><br>Until I get primal and some really nice NToV weapon, I will stick with my epics.<br><br>Also like Gazamel said. Kill Severilous yourselves, it feels alot better to have earned it then to make the war epic a shopping list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umuffildy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muffildy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 7:05:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> haste</span><hr size=1> war epic in general imo is not worth the effort required.<br>I mean, unless your in a guild where queen in chardok and serverilous is a cake walk; then dont bother.<br><br>theres plenty of slightly better/slightly worse cheaper weapons that you can buy; examples being swiftblade of zek, crescent blades of luclin, longsword of etherial energy, scimitar of emerald dawn, frostbringer etc etc.<br><br>and as for the haste thing (im prety sure this is proven someplace else as i recall reading it);  there is no minimum delay; so the faster your weapon in primary is the better bc of the dmg bonus; thats not to say that speed is the only thing that matters--ratio does too.<br><br>the only real good reason i can think anyone would spend 150k in addition to the time and effort/expenses of the other parts would be for the visual effect of the epic (it looks good!). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uurgetakildaogur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urgetakil da Ogur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 7:40:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/jordanzone/ff2/gifs/cecil.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> About 2 or so months ago i woulda said yes they are very worth it. Now....naa, i would use them for looks and the good stats it gives..but atm i am wielding 2 weapons that are alot better.<br><br>Urge<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36098>Urgetakil Da Ogur</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uelidib.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elidib</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 8:15:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> see, the thing you high end warriors (whom i notice already have your epics or better) are missing is that not every guild has access to sev/VP.<br><br>also, not every warrior has access to the scale even if it did drop, i don't know what your policies are on twinks, but in my guild a twink would never recieve that scale. well worth the money to a warrior's primary character if they knew they didnt stand a chance at the item, or getting any item better anytime soon.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uworrlorrd60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>worrlorrd60</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 8:26:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> I was in a guild capable of Sev and VP both... and yet i had to BUY my green scale. I pissed away 150k on it and banked the fuckin things a month later.  <br><br>Trying to justify completing the quest is a matter of: <br><br>1: Do you Main Tank when in a group or Raid ?<br>2: Do you plan on ever getting a weapon upgrade ?<br>3: Can you complete the parts needed without spending money ?<br><br>I personally would rather see the warrior epic burn in hell then to disgrace my hands by holding it once again. You can do better, and its not hard to do better. You can also be a royal pain in the raid to a raid if you are using it and are not the/a main tank. <br><br>Ultimately the decision is 100% situational and opinionated.   <p><img src="http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/8/8336/pages/19228/WebSig2.jpg" border="0"><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44344"  target="_blank">Profile</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utremainbladesinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TremainBladesinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 8:29:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theunholytrinity.org/cracks_smileys/cwm/big/firemad.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> The point is if you have 150k you can buy better weapons than epics (think willsapper/swiftblade of zek, both around 75k) so paying that just for the scale isnt worth it no matter what type of guild you are in. <p>"the day i die will be the day i shut my mouth and put down my sword" - Tremain, 55 Myrmidon</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 9:49:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/Kleg.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You'd rather have a 13/26 than a 10/20 under good haste, as they'll both approach minimum delay.<br>14/24, properly hasted is nearly as fast as any other sword in the game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I have heard this before, but what I haven't seen is any hard numbers to back it up.  I suppose I should go browsing through The Safehouse forums for more info.<br><br>Anyone know what the maximum delay number is that will still allow you to reach the haste cap?  Determining which is the best dmg/dly weapon would then be a matter of finding the one with the highest damage for that delay.  Procs and stats are another matter.<br><br>One question still remains.  Do the epics have higher damage bonus modifiers on them?  I read a post by Verant in which they stated they can adjust this number for each individual weapon.  And, when that warrior from FoH (Furor?) was the first to get his epics, he posted a SS of him crippling for over 1,000, in fact I think it was closer to 1,200.  That tells me the epic must have a high damage bonus attached to it.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uspitzohr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spitzohr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 9:58:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> Willsapper is No Drop <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>But yeah I think if you have the money to buy the scale you can get better/equal other weapons cheaper.<br>But of course, epic is a kind of status symbol <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27474" target="_blank"><img src=http://members01.chello.se/siv.lutz/Signatur.gif></a><br> Assassin of Landslide</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukhazad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khazad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 10:04:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> Depends if you do your epic as a shopping list, in that case that doesnt worth 150kpp yep. But IMO if you do it with your guild thinking about the symbol of epic, then yes it worth it. <br><br>Got my epic some weeks ago even if the stats sux I still really happy to get it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><p>- <b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=25762" target="_blank">Khazad Dum</a></b>, d0rf Crusader<br>   * member of <a href="http://62.13.29.72/landslide/index.asp" target="_blank">Landslide</a> *</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulummusl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LummusL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/23/02 10:44:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1>       Here is the skinny IMHO, about the Warrior Epic, from the stand point of one who has completed the quest and is still enjoying weilding the blades with a big goofy smile on my face. I could talk about being MT and aggro management etc etc, but I won't, because there is more to it than that. It took me about 6 months to complete, so it was no trival task and was started and completed post Velious release.<br><br>Going through the history of myself as a warrior, I was able to draw a few conclusions:<br>A) I tend to never carry the tag of any of the &quot;Top Tier&quot; guilds and my gear was typically average or below.<br><br>B) I tend to never have over 10K in the bank and was never fond of the process of aquiring EQ wealth in a liquid form (Hard Plat currency)<br><br>C) I am a student as well as a small business owner with an erractic schedule of having lots of time or almost none.<br><br>D) I am a stubborn jackass.<br><br>      I found myself in a guild of like minded folks, and we slowly built in strength to the point where doing an Epic of the caliber of the warriors was not out of the question, but areas like NTOV and Sleepers just were not on the map yet.<br><br>      Even though the fights at the time were very hard and took repeated attempts, components were slowly collected during events that were also part of getting other pieces for other Epics (Ragefire for Cleric = Red Scale, trips to the 3 old world Planes = Golem ball, Maestro's Hand, Spiroc Blade, Vox for Pally and Bard= Permafrost Block, Chardok Royals= Queen's Blade etc etc). What little money I had went to the Rebreathers and the Vox Ale.<br><br>     When it came down to Sev, I knew there was no way in HECK I was gonna ever save up enough bank to buy it, and then I was not sure if I would want to spend it all even then. I had some free time, so I made a little ranger mule, got him to lvl 10 with enough tracking range to have a good coverage area and parked him in EJ for 9 days. I would periodically check the Tracking but otherwise I busied myself doing normal day to day RL stuff. He popped once during a time when I had my ranger online but I was in bed asleep but the second time we gather the troops and took him down after 2 attempts. Not really an &quot;Uber&quot; tale of having slam dunked the Epic in a week, but it was a very fulfilling adventure in that it was truely &quot;Epic&quot;, complete with great victories and crushing failures.<br><br>The warrior Epic maybe obsolete now and bank trash to some or even in pocession of Mort or Gage for others, but I still consider it to be a great personal treasure and a great achievement for my guild. It will remain in service for long to come and I look forward to getting other warriors in my guild (we all share in the MT duties, depending on encounter) their Lightsabers as well.<br><br>So there you have it. Its subjective, depends on circumstance and how much you desire it.<br><br>Lummus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/24/02 10:53:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/jolly.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> I bought a piece for my epic.  I felt it cheapened the experience in no way.<br><br>Then again, after being to 23 Venril Sathir killings and never once getting the damn stick, I was getting a little tired of the epic quest and wanted that goddamn free rune.<br><br>And then yet again, it only cost me a JB BP, not 150k. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35824><img src=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/brain.gif></a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulummusl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LummusL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/24/02 5:39:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> Hey, its a free market. Arbok is asking 150k plus becuase he knows some jackass or jackasses will eventually pony up the money. Yes, it may take some time but someone will figure out how. Bare in mind though, most people who have that kind of dough now are those that are in the largest guilds that sell their FFA rot armor, and what use would they have for a weapon they gave to the banker a long time ago? There are also the Zerbrista's of the server that are crooks that will rob and cheat their way to the cash but will never find someone willing to hunt in Chardok for the Queen's blade. <br><br>It will all boil down to desire. There will be a hard working warrior or warriors in smaller, Non-National Brand guilds (other than Eternal Wrath(TM), Casus Belli(TM), Vea Victus (TM), Sphere of Transcendance(TM) or Landslide(TM) that will see the time invested in getting the cash together as being a better deal and better use of time than camping Sev for months or dreaming some kind of Veeshan's Peak pipe dream. <br><br>Lummus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usamuelledbetter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samuel Ledbetter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/24/02 8:58:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> IMO, the warrior epic isnt worth it because 95% of the warriors that have thier epics don't use them anymore, while all the other classes keep thier epics damn near forever.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umysthawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mysthawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/24/02 9:13:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> IMO, the warrior epic isnt worth it because 95% of the warriors that have thier epics don't use them anymore, while all the other classes keep thier epics damn near forever.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That is because the warriors that can &quot;easily&quot; get the warrior epic are in guilds that can also get better.<br><br>You generally don't see small guild warriors, or non-guilded warriors with their epics.  I don't care what anyone says, the Queen and Sev are extremely tough (Often out of range) for a small guild.<br><br>This doesn't make the weapons less worthwhile though.<br><br>*shrug* Just my opinion, take it as you will. <p><hr width="25%"><img src="http://www.eqsouls.com/images/msg/skorle-sign.jpg"><p><b>Skorle Thedrifter</b> - 60 GrandMaster <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif"><br><li>Officer of Heart of the Immortal Soul</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ulummusl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LummusL</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/24/02 9:34:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> You have to remember, those warriors that dumped their epics for better stuff also got them when they were a BRAND NEW concept. We are talking a few weeks after their introduction into the game. They have been ahead of the Bellcurve the whole damn time and with EQ being the world of things never needed to be replaced due to wear and tear, knowledge gained, assisted by equipment gathered= Permenant Advantage. They killed Chardok Queen and Sev before anyone else knew how, and thus had the ability to kill them over and over until they were done since there was no competition. Now they have moved on to big challenges and the upstarts AKA a bunch of other guilds have gotten strong enough to apply tactics that have leaked out over time to kill these targets. Just about any high level guild can kill Sev now so the competition is FIERCE. <br><br>Thats why the asking price on that scale has actually GONE UP.<br><br>Sorry gang. Blame VI for creating such a blatent, pyramidal caste system with their game design. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugazamel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gazamel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/24/02 9:53:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=20>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://arizona.speedchoice.com/~bbalatgek/pics/personal2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: haste</span><hr size=1> Almost forgot..  one thing to note about the warrior epic..  <br><br>If you use the new models, everytime you walk/run while wielding the 2h model, and the blade passes in your viewfield, you will experience a loss of graphics performance (ie, your screen will slow and/or stutter when rendering